  "title": "Touchdown Correlation",
  "difficulty": "Difficult",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">As the sport of football grows, teams are becoming increasingly interested in using statistics to better their teams. In a typical football game, a touchdown scored by a team is worth <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$6$</span> points. Suppose a team wants to make a graph for the number of touchdowns scored and points scored for their team. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">Which of the following would be the correlation for this data, assuming there are no extra points scored after each touchdown?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "0.06"
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "6"
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "−\n1"
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "1"
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "0"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
  "solution": "The <strong>correlation</strong>, <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6908-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mi>r</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32450\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32451\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32452\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.277em;\">r</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6908\">r</script></span>, gives the direction and quantifies the strength of the linear association between two quantitative variables. A correlation is considered strong if its value is close to <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6909-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>1</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32453\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32454\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32455\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6909\">1</script></span> or <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6910-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mo>&amp;#x2212;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32456\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32457\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32458\" class=\"mjx-mo\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.277em; padding-bottom: 0.441em;\">−</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32459\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6910\">-1</script></span>. \n\nIn this case, as the number of touchdowns increases, the number of points will increase by a constant <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6911-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>6</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32460\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32461\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32462\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">6</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6911\">6</script></span>. For example, \n\nSince points are increasingly constantly, the graph would be perfectly linear in a positive direction, as both variables are increasing. Therefore, the correlation would be <strong><span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6918-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32481\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32482\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32483\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.277em;\">r</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32484\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.058em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">=</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32485\" class=\"mjx-mn MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6918\">r = 1</script></span></strong>. \n\n<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is correct. ",
  "distractor_explanations": {
    "A": "<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is incorrect. Although points will constantly go up by <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6919-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>6</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32486\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32487\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32488\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">6</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6919\">6</script></span>, the correlation will not equal <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6920-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>0.06</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32489\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32490\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32491\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">0.06</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0.06</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6920\">0.06</script></span>. ",
    "B": "<strong>Choice 'B'</strong> is incorrect. The constant rate of change is <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6921-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>6</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32492\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32493\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32494\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">6</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6921\">6</script></span>, but this does not tell us the value of the correlation. ",
    "C": "<strong>Choice 'C'</strong> is incorrect. A correlation of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6922-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mo>&amp;#x2212;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32495\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32496\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32497\" class=\"mjx-mo\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.277em; padding-bottom: 0.441em;\">−</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32498\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6922\">-1</script></span> would mean a perfectly linear, negative association. Since both variables are increasing, the association is positive, not negative. ",
    "E": "<strong>Choice 'E'</strong> is incorrect. A correlation of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-6923-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>0</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32499\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32500\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-32501\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-6923\">0</script></span> would mean a very, weak linear association, and since points are increasing constantly, the correlation is perfectly linear."
